<b>
Description of the research project
</b>
<br>Research is focused on sequential assembly processes and 
regulatory pathways that govern the biogenesis, performance 
and acclimation of macromolecular photosynthetic protein 
complexes in the thylakoid membrane. Identification and role 
of translocon components, molecular chaperones and other 
folding factors in the thylakoid membrane, in stroma and in 
the thylakoid lumen during translation, insertion and 
assembly of chloroplast-encoded thylakoid membrane proteins 
are being addressed by proteome approaches. We also study the 
mechanisms how the environmental and metabolic cues modulate 
thylakoid redox reactions and thereby relay information 
signals to both the chloroplast own genome and the nuclear 
genome, ultimately leading to acclimation of plants to a 
changed environment. 
</p>

