<p>
<b>Chloroplast redox reactions in plant development and acclimation:</b> <br>


Environmental variables modify the performance of plant chloroplast and
thereby also initiate acclimatizing signal transduction pathways.
Photosynthetic light reactions activate a specific set of redox
components, which subsequently regulate the chloroplast function.
Recently it has been proposed that the particular redox reactions are
also involved in regulation of gene expression by initiating signal
transduction between the chloroplast and the nucleus. Our research aims
at studying the role of the redox components in chloroplast and in the
signalling processes including enzymes of protein phosphorylation, thiol
regulators and reactive oxygen species. 

